President Biden welcomed two Afghan leaders to the Oval Office, emphasizing that although U.S. troops may be leaving Afghanistan, support for the country will continue in terms of military, economic, and political assistance. The Afghan leaders expressed gratitude for the sacrifices made by American soldiers and discussed their commitment to unity and defending their republic. They also highlighted recent successes in retaking districts from insurgents. President Biden also briefly commented on the sentencing of Derek Chauvin, stating that the 22 and a half year sentence seems appropriate based on the guidelines.